  "text": "In order to enhance PBMC cytokine production, we also stimulated the PBMCs of the other 11 patients (nos. 5-15) with pollen extract at increasing concentration (20 mg/ml) and for a longer time (72 h). Under these conditions, we documented the higher release of certain cytokines, such as IFN-and IL-4, from the pollen-stimulated PBMCs on preliminary micro-bead assay. The concentrations of IFN-and IL-4 were measured by sandwich ELISA (DuoSet Sandwich ELISA, R&D Systems, Minneapolis, MN) to confirm the results obtained by the micro-bead analyses. (Table 1 ). It was found that the pollen extract suppressed IFN-release from the patients' PBMCs, but did not affect IL-4 production (Table 1, B) . Low allergen-induced IFN-secretion from the patients' PBMCs was also observed by Contreras et al. [CITATION_1] Of particular note in our study, we found that MEC markedly enhanced IFN-release from pollen-stimulated PBMCs (Table 1, C) . Therefore, it appears that MEC had an immunomodulatory effect in vitro.",
